 Q. Have you spoken to him about it at all?
 SERGIO GARCÃA: I did see Jose back in my home course in December, and I don't know, I think that he wants to be a captain. I'm not sure if he wants to be a captain for the next Ryder Cup, because he still feels like -- and we all feel like, he still has the game. It would be nice to have him as a teammate more than the captain for 2010, but we'll see what happens. 

 Q. In your opinion, why do you think he's delaying --
 SERGIO GARCÃA: I think it's not that. I talked to him and he said he would love to be on that Ryder Cup Team, but as a player, not as a captain. Two years from now, I think it might be a different situation for him, but I think we all feel like if he's healthy, he still has a great chance of making that team. So I would rather have him as a teammate than as a captain in the next Ryder Cup, if I could choose. 
 MICHAEL GIBBONS: Sergio, thanks for joining us. Good luck this week. 







